subject: twitter... no thumbs down on "Unlimited copyright license on your content"
text:
I don't think this should be a thumbs down.

Their license basically just gives them the rights to use it on twitter.com (or other 3rd parties).

"You retain your rights to any Content you submit, post or display on  or through the Services. By submitting, posting or displaying Content on  or through the Services, you grant us a worldwide, non-exclusive,  royalty-free license (with the right to sublicense) to use, copy,  reproduce, process, adapt, modify, publish, transmit, display and  distribute such Content in any and all media or distribution methods  (now known or later developed)."

...


"All right, title, and interest in and to the Services (excluding Content provided by users) are and will remain the exclusive property of Twitter and its licensors. "

They can't SELL your content for example.  

I think that should be a neutral issues.  At least for twitter.

Maybe there are hostile companies out there that want to resell your information though.
